<dd class='comment-body' id='Blog1_cmt-1176873350925912158'>
<p>
The blog Marginal Revolution has a piece dated April 19 th on bit coin.  Good links to other commenters also.<br /><br />The biggest problem I see (aside from how it works, of which I still have no idea, or why it&#39;s not a pyramid, or how it will be adopted by the computer less or computer illiterate)  is competition.  What&#39;s to stop someone from creating a whole new bit coin  &quot; peer to peer&quot; network?  Could eGold reformulate itself as a &quot; rival&quot;?  Could PayPal start offering a fixed number of credits for &quot; miners&quot;?
</p>
</dd>
