<p>
What &quot;backs&quot; a Bitcoin? It feels to me like everyone raving about BTC is thinking in terms of how much their currency is going to increase in value against USD. But what is it redeemable for?<br /><br />If you think an ever-strengthening transactional currency is a good thing for an economy, you&#39;re not thinking deeply enough IMO. Last time I heard, people wanting a job to earn an income, needed other people with an income who wanted to spend it on goods and services to keep other people in jobs.<br /><br />Currency needs to circulate freely, or there&#39;s quickly going to be a frozen economy with nobody earning an income. I don&#39;t care if the transactional currency is BTC or USD, or anything else. If it doesn&#39;t flow ... well, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=19Kr6hE3NWA" rel="nofollow">IMO it just won&#39;t give us all the warm fuzzies</a>.
</p>
