<dd class='comment-body' id='Blog1_cmt-8039145942054885668'>
<p>
Hello everyone. I&#39;m back after a long absence and glad to see we&#39;re moving to new topics and that spamming this blog stopped for the time being.<br /><br />On Bitcoin, I look at it from two perspectives:<br /><br />1. As store of value: it does not meet the focal point test &#8211; in other words since there eventually can only be one store of value that everyone agrees on, I do not see Bitcoin as being it for the entire world.<br /><br />2. As circulating currency &#8211; possible in a better world, but if we consider central banks still in existence and/or governments wanting to control the amount of currency (see unrestricted comments above) then it fails this test.
</p>
</dd>
